            <title>[GROOVY-696] Groovy misses first exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-696</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;===== Script: =====&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;def test() {&lt;br/&gt;
  println &quot;got here&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
  throw new Exception(&quot;blah&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1,2,3,4,5&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.each {&lt;br/&gt;
  test()&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;===== Expected Output: =====&lt;br/&gt;
got here&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;stack trace&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;===== Actual Output: =====&lt;br/&gt;
got here&lt;br/&gt;
got here&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;stack trace&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
