                            <comment id="14460768" author="blackdrag" created="Sat, 8 Jan 2005 15:55:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I cannot reproduce this issue. I&apos;m just getting the expected output.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460706" author="guillaume" created="Tue, 11 Jan 2005 11:46:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I get the exception the first time, but I get:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caught: groovy.lang.MissingMethodException: No signature of method GROOVY696$_run_closure1.test() is applicable for argument types: (java.lang.Integer) values: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be a plain Exception, not a MissingMethodException!!!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460692" author="phkim" created="Thu, 13 Jan 2005 09:36:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;// This is a workaround of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-696&quot; title=&quot;Groovy misses first exception&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-696&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-696&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
//&lt;br/&gt;
// The reason is fail to search the method &quot;test&quot; in a closure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;def test() { &lt;br/&gt;
  println &quot;got here&quot; &lt;br/&gt;
  throw new Exception(&quot;blah&quot;) &lt;br/&gt;
} &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1,2,3,4,5&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.each {&lt;br/&gt;
  // Insert a dummy code here:&lt;br/&gt;
  // a = test.class&lt;br/&gt;
  //       or test.class&lt;br/&gt;
  //       or test.class;&lt;br/&gt;
  //       or test.getClass() &lt;br/&gt;
  test.getClass() &lt;br/&gt;
  test() &lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460588" author="phkim" created="Fri, 14 Jan 2005 08:50:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This sample script code is similar to the above.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expect:&lt;br/&gt;
GOT HERE: 3*2 = 6&lt;br/&gt;
Caught: Exception: Fix me~&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Result:&lt;br/&gt;
GOT HERE: 3*2 = 6&lt;br/&gt;
GOT HERE: 3*2 = 6&lt;br/&gt;
Caught: groovy.lang.MissingPropertyException: No such property: run for class: groovy.lang.Binding&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Question 1: Why is &quot;GOT HERE: 3*2 = 6&quot; printed twice ?&lt;br/&gt;
Question 2: Why is MissingPropertyException catched, not Exception ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;--------------- begin of script ---------------&lt;br/&gt;
def someMethod&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/thumbs_down.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; { &lt;br/&gt;
  println &quot;GOT HERE: ${n}*2 = ${n*2}&quot; &lt;br/&gt;
  throw new Exception(&quot;Fix me~&quot;) &lt;br/&gt;
} &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;c = &lt;/p&gt;
{ someMethod(it) }
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;c(3)&lt;br/&gt;
--------------- end of script -----------------&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
